Reasoning: The paper introduces a framework for representation learning of protein sequences using bidirectional LSTM models and a novel similarity measure based on soft symmetric alignment. This work involves machine learning and natural language processing techniques applied to biological data, which suggests that the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses pairwise residue contact maps and global structural similarity information, which could fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions using natural language processing techniques, which could fall under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper deals with biological data and protein structure prediction, which could fall under the category of q-bio.BM (Biomolecules).
